        "answer_count": 5,
        "title": "Should I use XSLT or Java to transform my XML documents?",
        "body": "<p>I've got to transform a bunch of XML documents to another format.<\/p>\n\n<p>From what I can tell I can use XSLT or Java and an XML reader/writer. From past experience I remember XSLT being a slow, uphill struggle.<\/p>\n\n<p>Any recommendations as to whether I would be better off using XSLT vs Java + XML reader/writer to make these new XML files?<\/p>\n\n<p>Speed of transformation does not matter to me. This process will happen once for each of the 20 xml files that I need to process. I don't have to do this on an ongoing basis - in other words this process is throw-away.<\/p>\n\n<p>The output XML will be simmilar, simple XML. No swank.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 14983674,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "xml",
            "xslt"
        ],
